		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=339646"><span id=Scholar>dabuddaman</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />404 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.30]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=dabuddaman&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Seems like most people here are against PL.<br><br>I have to say, I am going to be the devil's advocate and vote for PL.<br><br>Now, before you rapidly press the reply button to refute me, hear me out.<br><br>The main reason many of you give against PL is the fact that you are not learning the primary role of a job. However, we all know the road to higher levels is not one easily tread. We cannot, and would not be able to receive a Power Level ALL of the time. The longest Power Level I have had was perhaps 2 hours. Now, when you figure 2 hours in the DAYS which many players devote to leveling up their jobs, it is hardly enough time for someone to actually not be able to learn their job. This game provides plenty of time for players to be able to become acquited (sp?) with their jobs, and a Power Level once in a blue moon would not dampen that seriously. Instead, a Power Level can allow the Exp grind to go by a little easier. Let people worry about only the SC which they are not familiar, or simply as a way to see how much damage one can honestly dish out without holding back.<br><br>Now, I also realize that new players, once they have tasted how much faster exp rolls in with a Power Level, would start to beg for more Power Levels, and that can be a problem. However, those n00b (yes, I am aware of the difference, and chose to use n00b) that consistently ask for PL can be reasonably assumed to also be players that would cut corners, not listen to others and think of themselve primarily as well. These combined traits all contribute to making them bad players, not we cannot solely blame a few hours of PL as the cause of all their inaduquacies.<br><br>Hence, I vote for PL, because I honestly do not see true harm being done by having a Power Level. I myself have received numberous PL in the course of leveling up various jobs, and so far, I have not been told by any party members that I am poor players despite having had some Power Levels.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Cay<br>Server: Remora<br><br>Main: Pld48/War24<br>Nation: Bastok Rank: 5<br>Craft: Cooking 60.0; Alchemy 50.0<br>PM: 1-2; ZI: 0; AF: 1[O], 2[ ], 3[ ], 4[ ], 5[ ].<br><br><a href="http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?83635" target="akztarg">http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?83635</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
