		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sat, Apr 9th 10:09 AM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=62&mid=11128912363301095&num=21&post=1&replyto=1113055720365294679"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=399528"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a> | <a class=sm href="mailto:Wondroustremor@allakhazam.com"><img src="/shared/mail3.gif" border="0" height="10" width="17" /> Email User</a>  <a name=1113055720365294679></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=399528"><span id=Scholar>Wondroustremor</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="100" width="85" src="/uf/Wondroustremor/Avatar1.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />336 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.62]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Wondroustremor&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ok- I've been unable to post for a little while (my job cracked down on internet access that wasn't work-related).&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm going throw in my two gil:<br><br>First of all, I'm really happy this topic (so far) hasn't devolved into a shouting match.  The General Discussion forum often has this topic spring up, and it usually turns ugly pretty quickly.  So good job on keeping it intelligent!<br><br>PLs, in themselves, are not evil.  They can be useful at times.  They can also be detrimental.  It's a matter of context.  However, I have personally received 4 PLs from friends in my entire time in FFXI (that does not include being in a party where someone else has brought a PL with them).  I have <i>never</i> asked for a PL.  And I have refused a number of PLs, because I felt that I did not know the role of my current job (be it thf, bst rng, etc) well enough for my liking.<br><br>Why? Everyone here has mentioned the obvious: you don't learn your role.  I won't repeat it- I think that Nalinn made the best analogy with his experience as a new NIN.  But, that is a part of the problem that arises.  I will expand a little:<br><br>Add to that your weapons and defence skills won't level properly.  Think about this: you hit mobs and get skillups.  With PLs, you don't have to hit as much most of the time, because you don't have to worry about pacing yourself.  Thus, things like your shield skill, block skill, ranged skills won't level as well, and you end up having to go back to skillup parties to make up for it.  And let's face it, who wants that WAR in the party that always misses?  Heavy damage is great, but not if the great axe never connects!<br><br>Also, in the PL parties that I've been in, the players get sloppy.  WHMs don't need to cast Heal, Protect gets neglected, and spells are haphazard.  BLMs overnuke because they think they will just be healed, so they don't learn the importance of pacing their spells.  WARs don't provoke every 30 seconds, and don't use Boost every 15 seconds if they're subbing MNK.  THFs have a harder time doing SA (and later SATA), because the hate keeps jumping from the &quot;tank&quot; to the DD to the PLer.  In general, if the party plyed <i>without</i> the PLer in the same way, they'd die a lot, and lose xp.  Since the PLer is there, they get away with it.  The longer (and more frequently) a player is in a party with PLers available, the more likely he or she will be as sloppy without one, because it takes practice to keep your skills and timing up to par.<br><br>Finally, I know everyone and their mother says &quot;back when I first started, things were different...&quot; BUT... When I first started, PLs were nowhere near as common.  I would get one or two parties out of a dozen that had PLers present- and I'm talking about the Dunes.  Now, I have to seek a party without one more often than not.  I can say that I am comfortable with my WAR, MNK and THF abilities and weapons/defense levels because I made sure I got as much exposure to PL-free parties as I could in the limited party experience I have had (I've said how much I hate the exp grind).  One thing I personally don't want is to join a party and realise that I'm the one that is the weak link.<br><br>So yes, go out and get an occasional PL if you wish.  However, be aware that PL parties are best used infrequently.  As Cay mentioned, most PLers aren't willing to do more than an hour or two at a time.  However, when one person in a party says &quot;My PL has gtg in 5 min&quot;, and someone else pipes up a second later with &quot;My PL is otw&quot;, it's time to look critically about the calibre of people churning out levels and where they'll end up.  They may end up killing you in later levels because they can't hold hate, or overnuke, or don't have critical skills up to par for their job.  <br><br>My final vote: Everything in moderation, but just say no to frequent PL parties.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Wondroustremor (Remora):<br><a href="http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?46812" target="akztarg">http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?46812</a> <br>No matter how the wind howls, the mountain cannot bow to it.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Bermuda</td></tr></table>
