		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.35]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Strangeone&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Zarath raises a very good point<br><br>I have had exactly one PL experience that was faster than a good party.&nbsp;&nbsp;This was way back on garuda.  One of my buddies was being pl'ed thru some levels in qufim, since we were bored, and my staff skill needed leveling, I decided to join.  I was like blm23 or so and he was some melee job of about the same level. forgot the exact job but he was armed with an axe - that I remember).  Since this was a roaming pl, even though I was a blm, I ended up doing mainly mele work with mb's on the sc's.<br><br>You're going &quot;wait a sec, blm... melee... wtf...?&quot;.  Yep it was a weird ass setup.  but it worked.  I rested when the pl needed to rest and since I was melee'ing I wasn't having the hate problems of most blms get so familiar with.  The sc's and the bursts compensated nicely for the lack of extra people and we were always on the move.<br><br>The thing here is that that was the only case in my memory where the pl was faster than a good party.  Most of the time it is usualy slower.  This is not the pl'er's fault, it's usualy the puller/leaders fault.  Also due to the lousy mob availability in the dunes - it's one of the worst places to PL in vanadiel.<br><br>Which raises the question if PL'ing is not faster than a good party, why do newbies do it?</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Strangeone - RDM/BLM (usualy) Tarutaru (always)<br>62RDM 32BLM 18SAM 17RNG 14WHM 13PLD 12DRG 11THF 11NIN 11BRD 10WAR 10DRK 10BST 8MNK 8SMN<br>60WoodC 60BoneC 47ClothC 17SmithC 8CookC 8LeatherC 