		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Apr 10th 6:40 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=62&mid=11128912363301095&num=21&post=1&replyto=1113172854604988312"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1113172854604988312></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=503315"><span id=Sage>Simp</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />80 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.78]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Simp&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Ok, so I've touched on some things in threads somewhat similar to this.&nbsp;&nbsp;But I'll put my 2 cents in here as well.  I am frequently asked to PL, and as a general rule, if you're asking me randomly, you're not going to get it.  Secondly, I don't think PL's hurt all that much, as long as, like has been said, it's done in moderation.  Leveling up your 4th, 5th, 6th, etc job gets to be tedious.  And I feel that as long as the people know their role, and still perform them, then everything will be ok.  I generally don't PL parties, simply for this reason; however, I PL many of my friends up to Lv. 10 - 12 so they can get into parties quickly.  Weapons will cap often 3-4 fights into the next level, because they're taking on T mobs all by themselves (so to speak).  Evasion wouldn't level as high, etc, but that's something that the person asking for a PL, has to deal with, and sacrifice in order to get to the level that they want.  I usually PL 6-10, and I just PL'd my freind's ninja to 10 not 2 hours ago.  <br><br>In reply to the poster who mentioned the WHM in the party feeling left out and useless.  I ran into this on the Carbuncle server.  We had a Lv. 66 PL, that was just throwing huge cures out everywhere, all my curing was doing absolutely nothing.  So, I just sat there, when afk and went out to get something to eat.  I returned to my computer to find myself a level higher, and the party still going strong.  A wholly empty experience I must say, so I decided to melee and level my club skill up.  When PL'ing keep that in mind.  <br><br>As a general rule, when I PL parties, I make sure they're made like a normal party, and I'll tell them to battle like they would, and I'll take turn with the resident WHM.  They take on two mobs while I watch, as a safety net.  To eliminate downtime, the WHM rests, while I take his place, and I try to take hate, just to make my job a little easier.  After that battle, the mages are completely rested up, and I sit back down for about few minutes, resting my MP and watching the party.  I would suggest this to people that PL.  They can get good XP, because the PT is set up well.  No one really loses that much in the way of skills, and the WHM won't feel useless.  You're simply there as a &quot;just in case&quot; for instance, the puller got aggro'd by a gob on the way back to camp.  And the WHM can safely rest, while you keep his party alive, and the process starts over again.<br><br>As for overnuking BLMs, I simply warn them, that my time is precious, and I refuse to cure a tanking BLM.  Learn to pace yourself, and not draw hate.  Once in a while, the BLM draws hate, that's fine.  But if I'm PL'ing, and the BLM is tanking 8/10 fights, I'll tell him one last time, that I'll a) let him die, or b) be on my way.  Often this ends with the leader, sometimes the BLM, saying I'm paying you, do as I say.  I can do without your 10k per hour my friend, but apparently you can't do without me.  I can earn that much farming to tele taxi'ing.  <br><br>Anyway, sorry for the long-winded post but I hope some will take my advice, and PL'ing won't be looked down upon as much...<br><br>P.S. Yes, when I walk through Valkurm, it seems at least 50% of parties now have a PL, it's sickening. </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />~Simplicity~ [Remora]<br>WHM55/BLM27<br>Cooking: 14 &gt;.&gt;<br>Fishing:&nbsp;&nbsp;3 m(_ _)m</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
