		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.30]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=dabuddaman&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>wow, I have no idea that so many people have PL in the dunes nowadays...mainly cause I dont ever really bother walking through the dunes...<br><br>In response to the exp/hr, imho, I think a PLed party would have much faster exp, given that there would be literally no downtime. The PLer would cast their cures, and when they run dry, resident healer take up the charge etc. This being said, I do have to agree that this would only be true if the party knows it's limit, and fight VT and occasional IT for exp chains.<br><br>On a side note, it is my opinion that most people no know fully understand how to obtaining faster exp/hr. Alot of people I run across seem to think that as long as each fight give ~180-200 exp, then the party is good, even though the party is barely making chain #1s and the down time is immense. To truly obtain great exp/hr, the trick is to use IT mobs to finish as higher chains. Specifically, start chain with a T mob, chain #1 with VT, chain #2 with IT, chain #3 with VT, chain #4 with VT if party can make it to chain 5 or IT if not. To have fluid exp chain is simply way better than to have 200 exp per fight, but 3 minutes b/w each fight for resting.<br><br>But hey, I think I'm preaching to the choir here ;).<br><br>Anyways, back on topic. The PLed party would have very fast exp/hr, especially in the dunes if they decide to go with exp chains. In fact, with a PL, the party can maintain the chains faster and longer, hence making having a PL viable. However, this is IF the party knows this.<br><br>Guess that's just about as much as I have to say on this topic. Great to see something that is hotly debated did not resort to alot of name calling and insults ^^.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Cay<br>Server: Remora<br><br>Main: Pld48/War24<br>Nation: Bastok Rank: 5<br>Craft: Cooking 60.0; Alchemy 50.0<br>PM: 1-2; ZI: 0; AF: 1[O], 2[ ], 3[ ], 4[ ], 5[ ].<br><br><a href="http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?83635" target="akztarg">http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?83635</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
