 so.. you do so for skill.. not for exp. I honestly think people party too much.<br><br>Most parties dont even know how to use a PL. they go for the IT's and they should be going for the T's .. so the exp isent that good.<br><br>Lastly most PL's in the dunes dont know how to do it very well .. so the exp isnt very good. (and if your reading this.. here is my &quot;homegrown&quot; method. Keep stoneskin up. Have the tank voke once. Have the white mage banish nuke or melee. wait for the tank to get to about 1/3 hp then cure him fully with one apporate Cure spell. You now have hate, so take a knee and rest till the end of the fight. rinse &amp; repeat.)<br><br>If your wondering, No, I dont PL people often, I've only done about 5 ever, and again none for money. Yes, I join n00b parties and sometimes die with them. Yes, I try to teach them and Yes, I actively work to make Remora a better place instead just complaining about PL'ers or Gil sellers.<br><br>End note.. I have no vote here. I could go either way but.. There are bigger problems then PL'ers.<br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Apr 21 05:31:42 2005 by Jadier</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />"OK, so ten out of ten for style, but minus several million for good thinking, yeah?" -- Jadier // Remora</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from REMORA</td></tr></table>
