		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.52]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=kenki&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Personally I don't like PL even if it's for me; I have 9 jobs pass valkurm dunes level and I still find it is possible to refine my skills as I level up more and more.<br><br>Most of the time when I see a PL and keep thinking if a new player is in the party: what would he be thinking about it later on? He'd think like &quot;Hey this PT sucks, I need a PL.&quot; rather than thinking &quot;Hmm... this doesn't work out, why is that?&quot;. Sound like they would be relying on PL. Then once they reach level 30, it's all about &quot;Can someone help me with this xxxx? {Reward}&quot; without even attempt to ask people they know during their lower levels (if they manage to make friends) and gather some people at similar levels to try it. It's hard to make friends if you don't go through some challenges together.<br><br>With some people charging for PL and Raise, new players will have the idea that if no {Reward} no {Help me out!} in Remora. This is depressing. There wasn't such a thing 2 years ago when English players are mostly lower levels. I don't even know when did the whole server start charging the people they help out.<br><br>Even for people at higher levels, they still refuse to look for a way to refine their skills. Any pld out there know that the more you tank as a pld the better you become at tanking no matter how bad you are at start. As you play other jobs you start having insights into those jobs (esp sub job) and reflect it into your main job you will notice what should you be doing to make the PT better. If you get a PL through those 10~20 levels then you'd probably not get enough 'real' experience on the job you level and won't improve.<br><br>This carries out to the missions and quests too. &quot;I just want to do it and be done with it&quot;.... These quests and missions reveal a great story line behind it and you just want to &quot;be done with it&quot;. Hire a high level player (a mage who can sneak/invisible you) and let him do everything, you just /follow and &quot;be done with it&quot;. I'd rather do it as a lower level party and have some fun even if we fail.<br><br> As people get deparate and offer {Reward} the higher levels will feel that it is about right to charge [this] much for helping [that] quest. &quot;I have people offering me 200k to help on this quest yesterday, so 150k {Reward} is about right.&quot; - Well, it's not wrong to ask for reward since they spend their time to help out someone unknown. But what important is that people somehow get the idea of an option {Reward} will gives you a better chance of getting high level help and be done with your quest.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
